Are school rules all right?

Are school rules all right? Well, that is not true. There are good rules that can manage the school better and also rules that are rather unfair. 

The first kind of rule I am talking about is dress codes. In my honest opinion, dress codes are not a problem and stop people from keeping up with someone rich, which will affect the learning experience. This also includes hair colors and all kinds of stuff. Some rules also shows a obviously unfairness, which I will describe in the next paragraph.

The most unfair rule, in my opinion, is requiring screen time on a school tablet. I used to use my school iPad for my project, and it stopped working, but my project was not completed. As a result, iPad screen time should be removed for undisturbed studying.

Finally, some rules can indeed help students to study much more easily, but some are just completely unfair.